  "prompt": "My interview in IOCL lasted for 30 minutes but the interview was below average.What are my chances of getting selected?",
  "response": "It's difficult to definitively predict your chances of selection based solely on the interview duration and your perception of performance. Several factors influence the selection process:\n\n1. Overall Interview Performance\n- While you felt the interview was below average, the interview panel might have a different perspective\n- They may consider various aspects beyond your immediate perception\n\n2. Other Selection Criteria\n- Technical knowledge\n- Academic background\n- Overall communication skills\n- Resume/CV details\n- Written test performance\n\n3. Potential Scenarios\n- If your technical knowledge and other credentials are strong, a relatively weak interview might not disqualify you\n- If multiple candidates have similar profiles, interview performance can be a decisive factor\n\n4. IOCL's Selection Process\n- Typically involves multiple rounds of evaluation\n- Not solely dependent on interview performance\n\nRecommendations:\n- Stay positive and confident\n- Wait for official communication from IOCL\n- If not selected, seek feedback for future improvement\n\nPrecise probability cannot be determined without complete information. Your actual chances depend on comprehensive evaluation by IOCL's recruitment team.\n\nBest approach: Wait for official communication and continue preparing for other opportunities.",
